   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-a" mid="196" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="162"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>Humans suspect everything and don't believe easily until they have seen it with their own eyes.<BR>But they are always deceived and are influenced by emotions and delusions.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-b" mid="197" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="163"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>...That's what someone told me last time.<BR>I'm not good with the human language. Even if I answer you, I'm not certain if they can understand me fully.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-c" mid="165" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Ask Stas's question)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-p" mid="166" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Ask Ithilien's question)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-2" mid="167" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>…I think I asked all the questions now.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="164"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>
…Now what else?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-d" mid="198" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="168"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>
He wants to know how dragons are born? As he has guessed, the <FONT color=#a82424>Black Dragon</FONT> was created artificially using the broken fragment of <FONT color=#a94407>Chaos Dragon</FONT>. In human terms, you can say that it was "man-made".</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-e" mid="199" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="169"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>But we, Argenta and I, are the descendants of the <FONT color=#a82424>Ancient Dragon</FONT>, so we have not been created by force.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-f" mid="200" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="170"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>The world created by Goddess <FONT color=#a82424>Altea</FONT> used to be beautiful and peaceful under the protection of the two dragons and the good Ancients. However, Goddess <FONT color=#a82424>Vestinel</FONT>'s jealousy brought darkness to the peaceful <FONT color=#a82424>Alcheringa</FONT>.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-g" mid="201" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="171"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>When Goddess Altea drank <FONT color=#a82424>Vestinel's poison</FONT>, the good Ancients became contaminated by darkness and started to turn corrupt. The evil Beyond Dragon who came from Vestinel's <FONT color=#a94407>Mistland</FONT> started to destroy Alcheringa.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-h" mid="202" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="172"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>Ancient Dragon and Chaos Dragon barely defeated the <FONT color=#a82424>Beyond Dragon</FONT>. But the Chaos dragon got <FONT color=#a82424>contaminated</FONT> by Beyond's evil energy. When the corrupted Chaos threatened the world once again, Ancient Dragon tried to stop  him. And the epic battle began....</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-h" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-i" mid="203" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="173"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>It was hard to say any of the two won. Due to the fight, Chaos Dragon's body was torn into pieces and was scattered all over the world. Ancient Dragon was also dying so it separated itself to prepare for the future.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-i" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-j" mid="175" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Then what happened to the other fragments of Chaos Dragon?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-j" mid="176" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Then can the other fragments be awakened into a dragon like the Black Dragon?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="174"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>
That's how Argenta and I were born. Our duty is to prevent the fragments of Chaos from being awakened as dragons. </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-j" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-k" mid="212" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="177"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>Since 50 years ago, starting from the Black Dragon, we have been looking for <FONT color=#a82424>Chaos's fragments</FONT> to seal them. Luckily, none of dragons were awakened. However, my power was not enough to destroy all the fragments.<BR>If Argenta and I become one again, then it might be possible to destroy all of them.<BR>Anyway, don't worry because those seals will never be broken unless I die.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-k" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-l" mid="213" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="178"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Can you and Argenta become one again?</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-l" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-o" mid="180" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>What is a Monolith?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-m" mid="181" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Argenta is here but how…?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="179"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>Hmm...<BR>We should try it first, but I think it's possible.<BR>But we can't do that now. She needs to support the <FONT color=#a94407>Monolith</FONT>...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-m" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-n" mid="204" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="182"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>…When <FONT color=#a82424>Argenta</FONT> and I were separated from the Ancient Dragon, most of the power went to Argenta. She is at least three or four times stronger than me. But she has to spend most of her energy on supporting the Monolith... So <FONT color=#a82424>Argenta</FONT> can't use her full power right now.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-n" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-b" mid="205" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="183"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>
Chaos fragments should have differences in power too. I don't know if any of them would be as strong as Argenta. Have I answered your questions?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-o" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-l" mid="206" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="184"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>The <FONT color=#a82424>Monolith</FONT> is a medium that connects the Goddess with this world.<BR>We have to support the Monolith so that this world does not break apart.<BR>That is all I can tell you for now.<BR>
<FONT color=#7e12d2>(Geraint doesn't want to talk about the Monolith anymore. Try asking something else)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-p" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-q" mid="207" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>It's the same for you too.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-q" mid="208" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Geraint, how about you?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="185"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>Someone from 50 years ago again….<BR>Although time has passed, everyone seems to be still bound by the past.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-q" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-r" mid="215" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="209"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>…….<BR>Right. I'm no different from them….</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-r" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-s" mid="216" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="187"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>After the battle 50 years ago, <FONT color=#a82424>Velskud</FONT> disappeared with the Black Dragon's jewel. I travelled around <FONT color=#a82424>Lagendia</FONT> to find him. Also, I had to find fragments of <FONT color=#a82424>Chaos</FONT><FONT color=#a82424>Dragon</FONT> to seal them.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-s" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-t" mid="217" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="188"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>After the <FONT color=#a82424>Goddess's dream</FONT> was contaminated by the poison of corruption, the world became more unstable. The contaminants spread all over the world and the monsters became stronger. Argenta had to spend more of her energy supporting the <FONT color=#a94407>Monolith</FONT> which was growing weaker and weaker.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-t" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-u" mid="218" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="189"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR><FONT color=#a82424>Argenta</FONT> was already exhausted by using too much of her power. But when she saw the <FONT color=#a82424>Second Star of the Ancients</FONT>, which notified the awakening of the Prophet, she went to Calderock Village to find the descendant of the Ancients.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-u" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-v" mid="219" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="190"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR>
<FONT color=#662500>You didn't say anything to anyone before you left?</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-v" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-w" mid="220" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="191"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>I didn't have enough time back then. After <FONT color=#a82424>Velskud</FONT> ran away with the Black Dragon's jewel, I realized it for the first time that there was <FONT color=#a82424>someone else</FONT> who had been after the jewel. Apparently, Velskud infiltrated into our army under that person's command.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-w" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-x" mid="221" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="192"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>I don't know.<BR>I roughly have an idea who it might be… but since I'm not certain, I don't see a need to talk about it.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-x" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-y" mid="222" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="193"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>…I have nothing to say even if they call me a traitor.<BR>They were fatally wounded and I didn't have the power to save them.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-y" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-z" mid="223" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="194"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>Wouldn't it have been better to leave and be loathed upon, since I couldn't save them?<BR>They say, <FONT color=#a82424>hatred is also a driving force for humans</FONT>...<BR>
I remember someone telling me that.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-z" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-1-b" mid="224" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="210"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR>
<FONT color=#662500>(I don't know what to say to him…)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n216_geraint_wounded-2" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n216_geraint_wounded-2-" mid="226" select_type="5" />
      <talk_question mid="11"><![CDATA[<html>$Geraint$<BR>
I told you too much.<BR>
Go and convey my answers to the person who sent the questions.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n088_scholar_starshy-2" image="QN_Npc_Geraint_silhouette.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Starshy.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n088_scholar_starshy-2-a" mid="230" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="12"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Stas$<BR>
You're back! Did you get his answers?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n088_scholar_starshy-2-a" image="QN_archer_nerwin_silhouette.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Starshy.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n088_scholar_starshy-2-b" mid="231" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="14"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Stas$<BR>I see. So the <FONT color=#a82424>Black Dragon</FONT> was only one of the <FONT color=#a82424>Chaos Dragon's broken fragments</FONT>....<BR>Then dragons can be made anytime unless all the Chaos' fragments are destroyed.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n088_scholar_starshy-2-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Starshy.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n088_scholar_starshy-2-c" mid="232" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Why?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n088_scholar_starshy-2-c" mid="233" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Why…</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="118"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Stas$<BR>Hmm… Thank you for giving me such precious information.<BR>I would love to see <FONT color=#a82424>him</FONT> and ask him for myself but I feel ashamed to do that.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n088_scholar_starshy-2-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Starshy.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n088_scholar_starshy-2-d" mid="235" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="234"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Stas${action:Talk}<BR>After the <FONT color=#a82424>battle 50 years ago</FONT>, I couldn't take his side. When he disappeared without saying anything, I was filled with anger and shock.<BR>
...I didn't look at the reality rationally.<FONT color=#7e12d2> (Stas hangs his head low)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n088_scholar_starshy-2-d" image="QN_six_heroes_silhouette.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Starshy.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n088_scholar_starshy-3" mid="236" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Stas….</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n088_scholar_starshy-3" mid="237" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html></html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="16"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Stas$<BR>I have done something a scholar shouldn't have done. When people tried to forget about things they couldn't understand and left only the <FONT color=#a82424>Six Heroes</FONT> in history, I should have stepped up and told the truth.<BR>…I should have...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n088_scholar_starshy-3" image="QN_Npc_Geraint_Closeeye.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Ishilien.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n088_scholar_starshy-3-" mid="239" select_type="5" />
      <talk_question mid="23"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Stas$<BR>…My questions have been answered.<BR>
Please go to Ithilien now.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-3" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Ishilien.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-3-a" mid="240" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="24"><![CDATA[<html>$Master Archer Ithilien${action:talk}<BR>Please tell me his answers. I'm listening.<BR>I've been waiting for answers to those questions for <FONT color=#a82424>50 years</FONT>.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-3-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Ishilien.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-3-b" mid="241" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="26"><![CDATA[<html>$Master Archer Ithilien$<BR>The balance of this world…<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Ithilien sinks deep into her own thoughts after hearing Geraint's answers)</FONT> </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-3-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Ishilien.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-3-c" mid="242" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="29"><![CDATA[<html>$Master Archer Ithilien$<BR>I understand now.<BR>They exist to protect this world.<BR>I knew they would have went through many hardships.<BR>But…</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-3-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Ishilien.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-3-d" mid="243" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="33"><![CDATA[<html>$Master Archer Ithilien$<BR>Still, would it have been too much to ask the dragons to understand how we felt?<BR>I'm not talking about difficult things like love or friendship.<BR>Me, Nerwin... everyone else must have felt the same.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-3-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Ishilien.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-3-e" mid="244" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="39"><![CDATA[<html>$Master Archer Ithilien$<BR>...
<FONT color=#a82424>Geraint</FONT> is really someone we can't hate.<BR>It would have been much easier if he had really betrayed us….</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-3-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Ishilien.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-4" mid="245" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="41"><![CDATA[<html>$Master Archer Ithilien$<BR>I could guess he would say that.<BR>I believe no one really hated him at the bottom of their hearts.. At least not me, and I believe it's the same for others.<FONT color=#7e12d2>(Ithilien smiles softly)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-4" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Ishilien.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-4-a" mid="249" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Are you okay now?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="46"><![CDATA[<html>$Master Archer Ithilien$<BR>Thank you for all your help, <FONT color=#387206>{user_nick}</FONT>.<BR>By the way, Bishop Ignacio at the Royal Castle seems to be looking for you.<BR>Please go and find him at the Royal Castle.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-4-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Ishilien.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-5" mid="251" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Not really sure but she seems okay)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-5" mid="252" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Fate… is that it?)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="250"><![CDATA[<html>$Master Archer Ithilien$<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Ithilien smiles)</FONT><BR><FONT color=#2b2723>Of course. Pala Telesia.</FONT><FONT color=#2b2723>…. Everything is bound by fate. They were just experiencing their fates being unravelled. I learnt that this is not something we should keep in our hearts. Thank you.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-5" image="QN_Npc_Bishop.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Ishilien.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n044_archer_master_ishilien-5-" mid="270" select_type="5" />
      <talk_question mid="269"><![CDATA[<html>$Master Archer Ithilien$<BR>Ignacio must be waiting.<BR>Please go and see him now.<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Go to Bishop Ignacio at Royal Castle)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n039_bishop_ignasio-5" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Bishop.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n039_bishop_ignasio-5-a" mid="272" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="271"><![CDATA[<html>$Bishop Ignacio${action:Talk}<BR>Welcome back.<BR>It's good to see your face when I am submerged with worries about this kingdom everyday.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n039_bishop_ignasio-5-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Bishop.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n039_bishop_ignasio-6" mid="274" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="273"><![CDATA[<html>$Bishop Ignacio$<BR>For now, we have overcome a crisis, but I don't know if an old man like me can do anything more for <FONT color=#a82424>Saint Haven</FONT>... These days, I cannot go to sleep because I worry too much about this and that.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n039_bishop_ignasio-6" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="NPC_Right_Bishop.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n039_bishop_ignasio-6-a" mid="276" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="275"><![CDATA[<html>$Bishop Ignacio$<BR>So... I was looking at <FONT color=#a82424>Dark Overlord Keep</FONT> with the Sage's Eye, and it seems like darkness has started to infiltrate that area.</html>]]></talk_question>
